{
  "texts": [
    "These models are designed to generate new sentences, word by word, using user input as a starting point.",
    "Training generative Chatbot models require a large dataset of sentences from real conversations.",
    "During this phase, the models learn the structure, syntax, and vocabulary of sentences in order to produce appropriate and coherent responses based on the received input.",
    "Typically, Deep Learning algorithms such as encoder-decoder neural network models are used, incorporating long-term memory mechanisms.",
    "One of the most widely used models in the field of AI Chatbots is the Sequence to Sequence (Seq2Seq) [7] model."
  ]
}